description.4: The First Appearance of Mr. Hyde!  While Thor pleads with his father Odin to be allowed to marry Jane Foster, Mister Hyde breaks into the office of Dr. Donald Blake and takes Jane hostage!
description.5: As never seen before! The Torch disguises himself as Spidey just so he can successfully scorch Sandman!
description.7: The origin of the Human Top, a.k.a. Whirlwind! Check out the Wasp's worst villain in his very first appearance. David Cannon has always abused his ability to spin really, really fast. And in his first bout of battle with Ant-Man and Wasp, destruction ensues!
description.10: Get ready for a rootin'-tootin' adventure starring the fastest draw in the West...Two-Gun Kid!
description.13: The First Appearance of the Lizard!  Spider-Man investigates reports of a strange lizard/human hybrid. Prepare for a showdown with one of Spider-Man's greatest villains, the Lizard!
description.16: Fury and his Commandos rescue the son of an English lord who has been captured by the Nazis and is forced to broadcast their propaganda.
description.17: Torch meets Captain America for the first time!
description.19: Hank Pym becomes Giant-Man for the very first time! Hank discovers a way to reverse the shrinking properties of the Pym particles. And just in time too- Wasp and Giant-Man must take down the Eraser, a villain who can quite literally wipe you out of existence!
description.22: The first appearance of Rama-Tut, later revealed to be Kang the Conqueror!
description.24: The Plantman tries to frame Doris Evans' father for robbing a store. Now, Johnny must work tirelessly to clear Mr. Evans' name! (note: this issue only contains the Human Torch story)
description.26: Ant-Man and Wasp encounter a new armored foe! Who is the man behind the Porcupine armor? Wasp suffers a blow in battle. Ant-Man must face the Porcupine alone!
description.27: Doctor Doom hears a J. Jonah Jameson’s news broadcast regarding the menace of Spider-Man. So, Doom sends a message to Spider-Man through his spider-senses which leads to an explosive meeting!
description.34: Millie has to make an important decision - fulfill her modeling assignment or attend her parents' anniversary party.
description.37: Sgt. Fury and his Commandos travel to Italy to rescue an army division trapped behind Massacre Mountain.
description.38: Attempting to improve his reputation, Johnny fights a villain that has stolen the mysterious Project X!
description.39: The First Appearance of Pepper Potts and Happy Hogan!  Happy Hogan and Pepper Potts join the cast, and Jack Frost is there to give them a COLD welcome! All part of the job when you work for Iron Man!
description.40: Petty thief and Jazz musician Trago inherits the hypnotic powers of a mystic. Now, the music that Trago plays controls the will of anyone who listens! How can Ant-Man and Wasp take down a foe this persuasive?
description.41: This is where it all began.  It's the X-Men vs. the Master of Magnetism!  The legendary  art of Jack Kirby's cover harks back to a more simple time for the masked mutants and belies the difficult and complicated future that is to come.
description.42: The First Appearance of the Sandman!  Spider-Man must contend with the villainous might of Sandman. But worst of all, Spidey has to deal with the dreaded...J. Jonah Jameson!
description.45: Millie goes to Rome! But it's not her luggage that appears to be lost…but her memory!
description.46: Surprise attacked by a creature named "The Raven", The Rawhide Kid finds himself out of ammo against a challenger who he may not be able to defeat even with the use of his gun!
description.49: The First Appearance of Baron Mordo!  Men call him Dr. Strange and speak his name in whispers.  But there is another who is more dreaded.  Meet Dr. Strange's arch-foe, the dreaded Baron Mordo!
description.51: There's been a recent lull in crime, so Ant-Man and Wasp decide to vacation in Greece! But what began as a retreat quickly becomes a super hero smack down; Ant-Man and Wasp take on the mythological Cyclops!
description.57: Join Sgt. Nick Fury in his fight against the Nazis! In "Seven Doomed Men", Sgt. Fury and his Commandos must intercept a large shipment and destroy it.
description.58: The First Appearance of Dr. Strange.  Meet a different kind of super hero - Dr. Strange, Master of Magic. When dealing with the occult and bizzarre, the Sorcerer Supreme Dr. Strange is the hero you need.
description.60: Egghead attempts a 'switch n' bait' when he kidnaps Wasp to lure out Ant-Man. But how did Egghead get ahold of Wasp in the first place? Ant-Man vs. an Anteater!
description.63: The man known as only as "The Sorcerer", unleashes Pandora's Box on Johnny Storm! The Human Torch must make his escape...and fast! (note: this issue only contains the Human Torch story)
description.65: The First Appearance of Janet Van Dyne, the unstoppable Wasp! While working for scientist Vernon Van Dyne, Hank Pym meets the young girl who will become his partner in crime fighting...and in life! Janet Van Dyne gains her sting, thanks to a super-powered transformation!
description.66: The Rawhide Kid defeated in a duel?! It can't be. With a quick-to-draw, advanced opponent like Mr. Lightning, The Kid faces his toughest one-on-one battle to date!
description.68: A jealous Human Torch wanted to derail Spidey's day, but now the hothead is helping the Wall-Crawler take down notorious art thief, The Fox!
description.72: The first appearance of Nick Fury.  On the frontline or in the trenches, Nick Fury’s elite squad of the Howling Commandos are a force to be reckoned with! The Resistance against the Nazis is now in France - will a young woman turn the tide for the Commandos? Following the earliest, legendary adventures of Nick Fury, war hero!
description.73: Gangster Tobin learns that the Human Torch is investigating him. Tobin then teams up with another foe of the Human Torch, the Painter, to end him once and for all! (note: this issue only contains the Human Torch story)
description.75: Ant-Man falls victim to the Time Master, and now he's aging much faster than he should! Will the villainous Time Master be Ant-Man's final undoing?
description.76: The First Appearance of the Vulture!  The Vulture's rampage in Manhattan begins. Can Spidey take down the avian menace?
description.78: The Fantastic Four plan their next adventure...sans Johnny! Feeling left out, the Human Torch decides to prove himself by taking down Namor on his own! (note: this issue only contains the Human Torch story)
description.80: Ant-Man takes on one of his strangest foes yet- a man who can control others with his hypnotic voice! But former preacher Jason Cragg doesn't use his abilities for good...as Ant-Man quickly discovers!
description.81: The enigmatic Watcher makes his debut in this very issue!  On a mission to the moon, the Fantastic Four meet Uatu, better known as the Watcher, who is tasked to watch humanity but never intervene in their affairs.  And on the way to the moon, the FF see a nearby Russian ship being hit by cosmic rays and the Russian crew are affected in a startling way!
description.82: Riding on horseback, The Kid faces an experienced gang willing to do anything to prove they can be the first to defeat the gun-wielding outlaw. The Kid was trained for situations like these, but will this be the time he makes a fatal mistake?
description.88: Enter...the Torrid Twosome! Johnny teams up with Carl Zante. He is then tricked into helping Zante break into a bank vault, and the rest of the Fantastic Four must step in! (note: this issue only contains the Human Torch story)
description.89: The First Appearance of Iron Man!  Watch his awesome approach! Listen to his ponderous footsteps as he lumbers closer... closer...for today you are destined to encounter - THE INVINCIBLE IRON MAN!
description.90: Ant-Man, whisked away to another dimension! Hank Pym discovers that fellow scientists have up and gone missing. Behind these disappearances? Kulla, war monger witch of the next dimension!
description.91: The FIRST issue of Amazing Spider-Man! The amazing Spider-Man swings into his very first starring series, fresh off of his debut in the pages of Amazing Fantasy #15.  In one of his earliest adventures following Uncle Ben's death, Spider-Man must save a crew of astronauts aboard a malfunctioning space ship!  Then, Spider-Man tries to join the Fantastic Four and then runs afoul of the Chameleon!
description.94: After the Wizard escapes from jail, Johnny Storm and Sue go after him! (note: this issue only contains the Human Torch story)
description.95: Ant-Man meets a worthy opponent in the The Hijacker, a supervillain interested in building a personal armory. When Ant-Man fails to save the day, who has he disappointed? A humbling moment for one of Marvel's mightiest heroes.
description.97: The Rawhide Kid may have finally bitten off more than he can chew, as the relentless Apaches and the dangerous Barker Brothers are hot on his trail!

0.text: Introducing the Blob! The X-Men's first try for a new recruit turns the mansion into a circus!

1.text: Peter Parker and Flash Thompson's rivalry comes to a head when the boys engage each other in a boxing match after school. But when a computerized menace interrupts the match, it's time for Spidey to swing into action!

3.text: The enigmatic Hate-Monger uses his hate ray to break up the Fantastic Four! Can Marvel's First Family overcome this mysterious enemy's strange ability? Guest-starring Nick Fury!

4.text: While Thor pleads with his father Odin to be allowed to marry Jane Foster, Mister Hyde breaks into the office of Dr. Donald Blake and takes Jane hostage!

6.text: Science battles magic...with new and better science! Mister Doll has Iron Man in the palm of his hand, and only an armor upgrade can break his grip!
Science battles magic...with new and better science! Mister Doll has Iron Man in the palm of his hand, and only an armor upgrade can break his grip!

10.text: Get ready for a rootin'-tootin' adventure starring the fastest draw in the West...Two-Gun Kid!

12.text: One of the Avengers is not who he seems! An alien agitator fragments the team almost as soon as it's begun!
One of the Avengers is not who he seems! An alien agitator fragments the team almost as soon as it's begun!

13.text: Spider-Man investigates reports of a strange lizard/human hybrid. Prepare for a showdown with one of Spider-Man's greatest villains, the Lizard!

14.text: Bull Barton wants his revenge. But when Kid Colt agrees to not use his arms for a month, will he break the vow to stop a robbery?

15.text: Thor faces off against the Human Cobra!

18.text: He's melting! Melting! Iron Man's burning with rage when the Melter moves in for the kill!
He's melting! Melting! Iron Man's burning with rage when the Melter moves in for the kill!

20.text: How can the X-Men catch an enemy who can be anywhere they aren't? Trouble appears when the Vanisher's on the loose!

22.text: The first appearance of Rama-Tut, later revealed to be Kang the Conqueror!

23.text: Lava Man has claimed New York City as the domain of the Lava Tribe, where he shall rule as king. That doesn't sit right with the Thunder God, so he heads to intervene!

25.text: Iron Man's first battle with an enemy in armor of his own! The Crimson Dynamo strikes!
Iron Man's first battle with an enemy in armor of his own! The Crimson Dynamo strikes!

27.text: Everyone's favorite neighborhood Spider-Man engages the Fantastic Four's most powerful enemy, Doctor Doom!

28.text: When two friends are torn between which of them gets to be sheriff, it divides the town…into two towns!

30.text: Kathy and Rick elope? Gasp! Scandal!

31.text: Patsy and Hedy find something they never expected to on a dude ranch -- romance!

34.text: Millie has to make an important decision - fulfill her modeling assignment or attend her parents' anniversary party.

35.text: Patsy turns sour and starts alienating friends and potential boyfriends alike. But is this really Patsy or a troublesome twin?

36.text: Thor defies the magic of Mad Merlin!

39.text: Happy Hogan and Pepper Potts join the cast, and Jack Frost is there to give them a COLD welcome! All part of the job when you work for Iron Man!
Happy Hogan and Pepper Potts join the cast, and Jack Frost is there to give them a COLD welcome! All part of the job when you work for Iron Man!

41.text: The master of magnetism has taken over a missile base, and only the strangest teens of all time stand between him and victory! It's the X-Men's first day of class, and Magneto wants to make it a memorable one - and their last!

This is where it all began.  It's the X-Men vs. the Master of Magnetism!  The legendary  art of Jack Kirby's cover harks back to a more simple time for the masked mutants and belies the difficult and complicated future that is to come.

The master of magnetism has taken over a missile base, and only the strangest teens of all time stand between him and victory! It's the X-Men's first day of class, and Magneto wants to make it a memorable one - and their last!

42.text: Spider-Man must contend with the villainous might of Sandman. But worst of all, Spidey has to deal with the dreaded...J. Jonah Jameson!

43.text: Sometimes there are threats too big for any one hero to combat. Stan Lee and Jack Kirby knew this. And so they created the Avengers, bringing Thor, Hulk, Iron Man and others together to form Earth's Mightiest Heroes. Avengers Assemble!

45.text: Millie goes to Rome! But it's not her luggage that appears to be lost…but her memory!

48.text: Dr. Zaxton is causing trouble with his duplicator ray. Can Thor stop him, or is he doomed to become one of many Thunder Gods?!

50.text: Chariots of Iron! Tony Stark's first time-travel trip allies him with Cleopatra herself against the legions of Rome!
Chariots of Iron! Tony Stark's first time-travel trip allies him with Cleopatra herself against the legions of Rome!

54.text: Witness the birth of one of Spider-Man's greatest enemies, the grotesque Dr. Octopus!

56.text: Thor and Loki join forces...for evil!

59.text: Iron Man battles a menace to Earth...which comes from within it! Nemesis from the Netherworld! (Originally published as TALES OF SUSPENSE (1963) #43)
Iron Man battles a menace to Earth...which comes from within it! Nemesis from the Netherworld!

61.text: The Fantastic Four battle the Mad Thinker and his awesome Android! The Android...neither animal, nor vegetable, nor mineral...what is it?!

62.text: Thor's powers are useless against the Radioactive Man, who uses his own strange abilities to hypnotize the God of Thunder! Can the Odinson break free from the oppressive power of this Communist Monster from the East?!

64.text: The Red Barbarian is at the gate, and he wants Iron Man's secrets! The golden gladiator against his first "red menace!" (Originally published as TALES OF SUSPENSE (1963) #42)
The Red Barbarian is at the gate, and he wants Iron Man's secrets! The golden gladiator against his first "red menace!"

70.text: The Puppet Master has gained control over the Sub-Mariner and hatches a plan to finally ensnare and defeat the Fantastic Four.

71.text: Thor's hammer has been stolen! Who is responsible for this treacherous deed and will Thor be able to retrieve his mighty weapon?

74.text: The original Dr. Strange comes not to save the world, but to destroy it! Iron Man vs. one of the maddest scientists ever! (Originally published as TALES OF SUSPENSE (1963) #41)
The original Dr. Strange comes not to save the world, but to destroy it! Iron Man vs. one of the maddest scientists ever!

76.text: The Vulture's rampage in Manhattan begins. Can Spidey take down the avian menace?

77.text: Loki increases Sandu the Mystic's power a thousand fold! How can the Odinson hope to defeat this city-stealing madman?

79.text: Gray goes gold when Tony Stark gives his armor a new look, just in time to face a prehistoric powerhouse! Iron Man vs. his first super-powered opponent!  (Originally published as TALES OF SUSPENSE (1963) #40)
Gray goes gold when Tony Stark gives his armor a new look, just in time to face a prehistoric powerhouse! Iron Man vs. his first super-powered opponent!

81.text: More than two hundred thousand miles from Earth, the Fantastic Four face the menace of The Red Ghost!

85.text: General Ross tasks the Fantastic Four with finding and capturing the Hulk. But treachery is afoot and the Hulk sets out to find the real villain of the day...the Wrecker!

86.text: If the Hulk can't handle the Metal Master, it could mean the end of the human race!

89.text: Iron Man's first explosive appearance by Stan Lee and Jack Kirby. 'Nuff said. (Originally published as TALES OF SUSPENSE (1963) #39)
Iron Man's first explosive appearance by Stan Lee and Jack Kirby. 'Nuff said.
In a war-torn land, Tony Stark builds the world's greatest warrior...around himself! The debut of Iron Man!

91.text: Spider-Man, in one of his earliest adventures following Uncle Ben's death, must save a crew of astronauts aboard a malfunctioning space ship!
What's left to be said about Steve Ditko and Spider-Man? Spidey's Spidey, due in large part to Ditko's early contributions, including this cover to the first all-Spider-Man comic.

92.text: When a teenage boy gets a personal genie, the entire planet becomes subject to his will!

93.text: At last the Fantastic Four meet a foe whose power is even greater than theirs! Here is: The Impossible Man!

96.text: Donald Blake is forced to treat Thug Thatcher's injuries at gunpoint. The good doctor must find a way to transform into Thor and dispatch the villainous swine!
